        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 13 at 3:16PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Jemison, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbiana, Jemison, Wilsonville, Talladega Springs, Thorsby,
Fayetteville, Strickland Crossroads, Marble Valley, Lay Lake, Lay
Lake Dam, Shelby, Beeswax Creek Park, Alabama 4H Center, Cedar Creek,
Shelby Shores, Waxahatchee Creek, Highway 145 and CR 46, Paint Creek,
Kelley Branch, and Spring Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
